text: Seyed Ali Ahmadzadeh (born September 11, 1964) is an Iranian lawyer and politician. Ahmadzadeh is the 21st Governor of Kohgiluyeh and Boyer-Ahmad province since September 22, 2021. He was the Vice Governor of Qom province for Economic Affairs from 2005 through 2009. Ahmadzadeh was elected as the governor of Gachsaran city in 1994, and then in 1998, he became the vice president of Qom University for Economic Affairs and worked until 2005. == References == == Other websites == Category:Iranian politicians Category:Iranian lawyers Category:Iranian people Category:1964 births
